Lagos State yesterday recorded one new COVID-19 related death, bringing to 19, the total number of deaths recorded in the state. This was disclosed on the official twitter handle of the state Ministry of Health @LSMOH which disclosed that five previously confirmed COVID-19 patients had been transferred to Ogun State, bringing to 13, the total number of cases transferred from the state. According to the ministry, COVID-19 update in the state shows that 80 new cases were confirmed on April 24, 2020, raising the total confirmed cases to 670 out of which 117 have recovered and have been discharged with 19 deaths recorded.  Two more COVID-19 deaths recorded in Lagos Two more COVID-19 deaths recorded in Lagos Another COVID-19 patient dies of complications in Lagos